  "description": "The chunky heron had a thick, all dark bill, longish (for a night-heron), thickish neck with dull yellowish legs, brown-gray back with small whitish spots. The throat and breast had light grayish vertical streaks and the undertail coverts were white. From my distant photos, it looks like the iris is yellowish orange.Behaviors: It stood quietly just out in view from the cattail marsh and pond where it was located.  Never saw it move more than its head.Call: None heardPlumage: juvenile",
